OL,3,CSoftware provider facing #6m fine over
OL,4,Cransomware attack that hit NHS services
OL,6,FThe UK's data protection watchdog said
OL,7,Fit has provisionally decided to fine a
OL,8,Fsoftware provider just over #6 million
OL,9,Fover a 2022 ransomware attack that
OL,10,Fdisrupted NHS and social care services.
OL,12,FThe Information Commissioner's Office
OL,13,F(ICO) said it had provisionally found
OL,14,Fthat Advanced Computer Software Group
OL,15,Fhad failed to implement measures to
OL,16,Fprotect the personal information of
OL,17,F82,946 people who were affected by the
OL,18,Fattack, which included some sensitive
OL,19,Finformation.
